cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.COMM, cs.MM 

This paper deals with information theory and communication networks, specifically interference channels and network coding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses relay nodes and their role in improving communication rates, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes and bit-interleaved coded-modulation (BICM) suggests cs.SI (Signal Processing) as another possible category. The paper also discusses the use of a shared out-of-band link, which falls under cs.COMM (Computer Communications and Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a structured binning scheme, which could potentially fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
